        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 14 at 3:38PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 338 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northwest of Deerlick Creek Campgrounds, or 8 miles north of
Holt, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Northern Tuscaloosa, Northport, Holt, Lake View, Brookwood, Vance,
Tannehill Ironworks State Park, Bull City, Abernant, Deerlick Creek
Campgrounds, Mercedes Benz Of Alabama, Bankhead Lock And Dam, North
Bibb, Lake Tuscaloosa, East Brookwood, Windham Springs, Peterson,
Lake Harris, Lake Nicol, and Caffee Junction.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
